    "body": "## Description\r\n\r\ncloses #265 \r\n\r\nThis PR implements a non deterministic reduce that use atomics. Currently, it only supports `cuda::std::plus<>` and contiguous `OutputIteratorT`s (since we are calling `atomicAdd`). If these conditions are not fulfilled it falls back to the default reduce. \r\n\r\n## Performance results\r\n<img width=\"4472\" height=\"3544\" alt=\"H200_reduce_sum\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/caaac6a4-1c32-44ad-b441-748703c53c4d\" />\r\n\r\n<img width=\"4472\" height=\"3544\" alt=\"B200_reduce_sum\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/d22b9d26-c2c9-4a36-967e-a492fad33981\" />\r\n\r\n## Checklist\r\n- [X] New or existing tests cover these changes.\r\n- [ ] The documentation is up to date with these changes.\r\n",
    "created_at": "2025-06-11T19:54:32Z",
